<h2 id="lesson-2-drinking-bird-blueprints">Lesson 2: Drinking Bird Blueprints</h2>

<p><a href='/wiki/w/image/view?key=agpzfnVkYWNpdHl1chILEglXaWtpSW1hZ2UY-ZawQAw' title='agpzfnVkYWNpdHl1chILEglXaWtpSW1hZ2UY-ZawQAw;size=500'><img src='//lh3.googleusercontent.com/OLOEUaAI7odnMfIMIzBKoerGe-al_IEWMF2bwsp2BrxGujUQSyDO0q7YLQgtx-_0vnrnj96pOrCGJAzDWDs=s500' alt='blueprint_front.png'/></a> <a href='/wiki/w/image/view?key=agpzfnVkYWNpdHl1chILEglXaWtpSW1hZ2UYs7jCQAw' title='agpzfnVkYWNpdHl1chILEglXaWtpSW1hZ2UYs7jCQAw;size=500'><img src='//lh3.googleusercontent.com/jIgQKlO17nmFKIN6NW9x6piZxi8oPeIloQlk2K1I3eUkKvZ129HJAZUpsyQVyToQdkL_dcaHmstFUD8B=s500' alt='blueprint_side.png'/></a></p>

<p>Note that, confusingly, the world's +X axis goes from right to left in the drawing on the right. In other words, the bird is facing down the -X axis in the exercise.</p>

<p>Reference images (follow the blueprints, not these photos):</p>

<p><a href='/wiki/w/image/view?key=agpzfnVkYWNpdHl1chILEglXaWtpSW1hZ2UY1pO_QAw' title='agpzfnVkYWNpdHl1chILEglXaWtpSW1hZ2UY1pO_QAw;size=500'><img src='//lh3.googleusercontent.com/5pSNpWOl3Mn7L0MS4i1c80RjB64shmjMG8zIsT_RsQBuDd1bjitKy24ENXBCv9hON3yIaPekQPTcoHDFWQ=s500' alt='db_front_photo.jpg'/></a> <a href='/wiki/w/image/view?key=agpzfnVkYWNpdHl1chILEglXaWtpSW1hZ2UY2ZjCQAw' title='agpzfnVkYWNpdHl1chILEglXaWtpSW1hZ2UY2ZjCQAw;size=500'><img src='//lh3.googleusercontent.com/fEA_PDuEJV5d3pnOVSgJISK7s283Qsp9JbTrBmtqDz7iluu6ooZCljjXH7oPYKLaDemxBySxSwfwWotVUD0=s500' alt='db_side_photo.jpg'/></a></p>

<p>So that the exercise passes, and the spheres and cylinders look good,
all SphereGeometry calls should be of the form:</p>

<pre><code class="prettyprint">SphereGeometry( radius, 32, 16 );
</code></pre>

<p>and CylinderGeometry calls should be of the form:</p>

<pre><code class="prettyprint">CylinderGeometry( radiusTop, radiusBottom, height, 32 );
</code></pre>
